author: Brian Costa
title: Tiger Woods Doesn’t Get the Win, But Tigermania Is in Top Form
text:
At the Presidents Cup, where he was an assistant captain for the U.S. team, Tiger Woods was asked if he could envision a scenario in which he never returned to competitive golf. “Yeah, definitely,” he said, in what was less a concession than a confirmation of the obvious: Beset by back problems, Woods looked like he might be finished.
That was a little over five months ago, which underscores the most staggering thing about what has transpired since. It’s not merely that Woods is healthy again, which was the point of undergoing...
